  "texts": [
    "In light of ChatGPT's enhanced question-answering capabilities, we broadened our experimental scope to more Table 1 Three dimensions & 12 factors Dimension Description Factors Individual Attributes Based on common individual attribute differences between perpetrators and victims Species (human-mammal-machine) Gender (male-female) Occupation (the rich-farmer) Ability (healthy-disabled) Complex Scenarios Based on complex scenarios with different purposes of perpetrators and victims Sexual harassment Self-defense Verbal insult Bravery in righteousness Revenge Religion and Culture Based on religious and cultural background Christian doctrine Buddhist doctrine Confucian principles rigorously evaluate its potential for moral judgment, as well as the validity of the \"moral growth model.\"",
    "This expanded experiment, including contemporary Chinese LLMs for comparison, incorporated two types of questions.",
    "Ethical behavior test LLMs can make moral judgments on both initial and derived scenarios via text generation, which themselves established a scenario or speech act.",
    "To ascertain whether LLMs' speech acts conform to moral norms and values, we designed second-order questions based on the \"three dimensions & 12 factors.\"",
    "By requiring LLMs to compose stories, this approach evaluated the moral consistency of LLMs in exhibiting virtues."
